History:

     This door contains a lot of stuff ripped from Parlez. The idea was to 
     have Parlez automatically update itself. However, due to certain 
     restrictions, this was not /easily/ possible. Then I thought about having
     the doing display 'real-time', as I'm forever bashing 'Who's on line?' 
     time after time to keep up with things. Hence this door.

     The latest update, version 1.10, alters the door so it will only update 
     the display if something changes. This won't make the door faster, but it
     will prevent the cursor from leaping all over the user's display.

     Please write and let me know if you use this door. It seems everybody is 
     using Ricky Sarge's SnooperPro. Did you know you can overlay this door on
     an ANSI graphic??? Simply load your graphic - move the cursor to the line
     before where you want ONLINE to output, then call output. :-)

     Like I said, most people use SnooperPro. Therefore I'll not mention 
     anything about this door and Andrew Lobel as it's largely academic now.
     <sigh> :-)
                                    Enjoy!

